        "content": "<p>I have three elements, <code>x, y, z</code> of a LinearOrder, and I want to split to the 6 cases <code>x ≤ y ≤ z</code>, <code>x ≤ z ≤ y</code>, ...<br>\nWhat's the nicest way to do this?</p>",
        "id": 459363305,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1723178041
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>obtain hxy | hyx := le_or_lt x y &lt;;&gt; obtain hyz | hzy := le_or_lt y z &lt;;&gt; obtain hzx | hxz := le_or_lt z x</code>, then eliminate the 2 out of 8 cases that are impossible</p>",
        "id": 459378991,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1723183965
    },
